<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Be As a City Upon a Hill</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="3" relname="attribution">" For we must consider</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1004" relname="span">that we shall be as a city upon a hill .</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1005" relname="same_unit">The eyes of all people are upon us ,</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1006" relname="same_unit">so that</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1008" relname="span">if we shall deal falsely with our God in this work</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="elaboration">we have undertaken ,</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="9" relname="attribution">and so cause Him to withdraw His present help from us ,</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1009" relname="span">we shall be made a story and a by-word through the world . "</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1003" relname="attribution">-- John Winthrop , " A Model of Christian Charity "</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1012" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="sequence">Show mercy and justice in equal parts .</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1014" relname="span">Sometimes there may be an occasion</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1015" relname="joint">of showing mercy to a rich man in some sudden danger of distress ,</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1015" relname="joint">and also doing a mere justice o a poor man in regard of some particular contract . .</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1016" relname="joint">First , accept that every man afford his help to another in every want or distress .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="span">Second ,</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1020" relname="span">that he perfomed this out of the same affection</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="18" relname="elaboration">which makes him careful of his own goods ,</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1020" relname="attribution">according to that of our Savior .</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1021" relname="sequence">Give .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="23" relname="condition">If the time and occasion are extraordinary ,</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1023" relname="span">give out in abundance .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="25" relname="condition">If the time and occasion are extraordinary ,</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1025" relname="span">be ruled by them .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1021" relname="sequence">Lend .</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="span">Observe whether or not the recipient has present , probable , or possible means</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="27" relname="elaboration">of repaying you .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1031" relname="condition">If he does not ,</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1031" relname="span">then give him according to his necessity</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1032" relname="span">rather than lend him</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="31" relname="manner">as he requires .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1036" relname="span">If he has means</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="33" relname="elaboration">of repaying you ,</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1035" relname="span">do not look at the act as a mercy ,</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1037" relname="span">but a way of commerce</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="36" relname="elaboration">in which you are ruled by justice .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1029" relname="joint">Forgive .</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1041" relname="condition">Whether you lended as an act of mercy or as a way of commerce ,</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1041" relname="span">you must forgive him</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="40" relname="concession">regardless of whether or not he repays you .</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1043" relname="preparation">Love .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1044" relname="span">The love among Christians is a real thing ,</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="43" relname="elaboration">not imaginary .</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1043" relname="joint">This love is as absolutely necessary to the being of the body of Christ</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1047" relname="preparation">as the sinews adn other ligaments of a nutural body are to teh being of that body .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1047" relname="joint">This love is divine , spiritual nature free , active , strong , courageous , permanent .</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1048" relname="span">Undervaluing all things beneath its proper object .</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="48" relname="elaboration">Of all the graces , this makes us nearer to resemble the virtues of our Heavenly Father .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1050" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1054" relname="attribution">Accept</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1054" relname="span">that God Almighty hath ordained the condition of mankind :</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1055" relname="span">That some must be rich ,</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1056" relname="span">some poor ,</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1057" relname="span">some high and powerful ,</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="55" relname="elaboration">others low and subjected .</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1059" relname="attribution">Through this , you will be able to acknowledge</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1060" relname="preparation">that :</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="60" relname="preparation">See the glory of His wisdom in the variety and difference of the creatures , and the glory of His power ,</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1060" relname="span">in ordering all these differences for the preservation and good of the whole .</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1062" relname="preparation">See</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1062" relname="span">that He might have the more occasion</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1063" relname="span">to manifest the work of His Spirit upon teh wicked</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="63" relname="elaboration">in moderating and restraining them .</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1066" relname="preparation">See</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1066" relname="joint">that every man might have need of others ,</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1066" relname="joint">and from hence they might al be knit more nearly together in the bonds of brotherly affection .</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1068" relname="span">Know the proper time and place</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1069" relname="joint">to sell all</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1069" relname="joint">and give to the poor .</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1071" relname="span">Know the proper time</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="71" relname="purpose">to give beyond your ability .</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1073" relname="span">Know the proper time</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="73" relname="purpose">to unite with the community in some special service for the Church .</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1075" relname="span">Know the proper time</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="75" relname="purpose">to help anyone in distress beyond your ability ,</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1076" relname="span">rather than tempt God</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="77" relname="circumstance">in putting him upon help by miraculous and extraordinary means</segment>
